    "about": "Akastor ASA is a Norway-based oilfield services investment company with a portfolio of industrial holdings. Its origins trace to Akers Mekaniske Verksted, founded in Oslo in 1841. The company was established as an independent investment vehicle in September 2014 following a demerger from Aker Solutions ASA. Akastor operates through four segments: HMH (drilling systems and lifecycle services — a premier offshore drilling equipment provider formed by combining MHWirth and Halliburton's drilling division); AKOFS Offshore (vessel-based subsea well construction and intervention services); DDW Offshore (three AHTS vessels); and Other Holdings. Akastor has a flexible mandate for active ownership and long-term value creation, with operations across Norway, the US, Brazil, Singapore, the Middle East, and Australia.",
